{"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/swastishankhdhar/hysplit-receptor-assignment-geopandas-folium?scriptVersionId=336698722\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"attachments":{"2beb56d7-c70e-4d05-9d27-6e42b4308ab4.png":{"image/png":""},"2d8f2da9-c00b-4ed3-89c7-22fc5550a1e6.png":{"image/png":""},"2f8effcc-faa5-4db8-ac4c-05e3ada24c8d.png":{"image/png":""}},"cell_type":"markdown","id":"323f6175","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.007795,"end_time":"2026-07-20T13:04:50.111516+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-20T13:04:50.103721+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# WORKFOLW\n","HYSPLIT .tdump files (one per day, full year)\n","\n","    Parse → trajectory points (lat, lon, time, alt)\n","      \n","    Spatial Join → which US county is each point in\n","            \n","    Compute transport weight per county per day\n","            \n","    Match to PM2.5 data (county + date)\n","            \n","    Build transport-weighted PM2.5 variable\n","            \n","    Regression: predict LA PM2.5 from transport-weighted PM2.5\n"," \n","![image.png](attachment:2beb56d7-c70e-4d05-9d27-6e42b4308ab4.png)\n","\n","Folium makes it easy to visualize data that’s been manipulated in Python on an interactive leaflet map. It enables both the binding of data to a map for choropleth visualizations as well as passing rich vector/raster/HTML visualizations as markers on the map.\n","\n","The library has a number of built-in tilesets from OpenStreetMap, Mapbox, etc, and supports custom tilesets. \n","Folium supports both Image, Video, GeoJSON and TopoJSON overlays and has a number of vector layers built-in.\n","Key Features and Uses\n","\n","Interactive Maps: Allows users to zoom, pan, and click on map elements for information.\n","\n","Data Binding: Supports choropleth maps (where colors correspond to underlying data values) and custom GeoJSON/TopoJSON overlays.\n","\n","Markers and Popups: Enables adding custom pins, tooltips, popups, and heatmaps to highlight specific locations.\n","\n","No Web Development Required: Allows users to generate rich, interactive web maps as standalone HTML files without writing a single line of HTML, CSS, or JavaScript.\n","\n","example- \n","    import folium\n","\n","# Create a map centered at a specific location\n","m = folium.Map(location=[19.0760, 72.8777], zoom_start=12) # Centered in Mumbai\n","\n","# Add a marker\n","folium.Marker(\n","    location=[19.0760, 72.8777],\n","    popup='Mumbai',\n","    tooltip='Click here'\n",").add_to(m)\n","\n","# Save or display the map\n","m.save('index.html')"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"id":"bc709b2c","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"b1076dfc-b9ad-4769-8c92-a6c4dae69d19","_uuid":"8f2839f25d086af736a60e9eeb907d3b93b6e0e5","execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-20T13:04:50.124922Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-20T13:04:50.124617Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-20T13:04:51.98114Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-20T13:04:51.980238Z"},"papermill":{"duration":1.864997,"end_time":"2026-07-20T13:04:51.982963+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-20T13:04:50.117966+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["/kaggle/input/datasets/swastishankhdhar/tdump-file-hysplit/tdump.112524.txt\n","/kaggle/input/datasets/swastishankhdhar/pm2-5-usa-2020/county_day_ushigh_pm25_2020.csv\n"]}],"source":["import numpy as np # linear algebra\n","import pandas as pd # data processing, CSV file I/O (e.g. pd.read_csv)\n","import os\n","for dirname, _, filenames in os.walk('/kaggle/input'):\n","    for filename in filenames:\n","        print(os.path.join(dirname, filename))\n","\n","import kagglehub\n","# kagglehub.dataset_download('<owner>/<dataset-slug>')\n","import geopandas as gpd\n","from shapely.geometry import Point\n","# from shapely.geometry import Point: Imports a specific \n","# blueprint to create explicit coordinates. Shapefiles and geographic maps cannot understand a plain text latitude and longitude column until you explicitly bundle them into a Python Point object."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"id":"bc3bc2c8","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-20T13:04:51.997369Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-20T13:04:51.996773Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.120869Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.119972Z"},"papermill":{"duration":1.132913,"end_time":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.122722+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-20T13:04:51.989809+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["pm=pd.read_csv('/kaggle/input/datasets/swastishankhdhar/pm2-5-usa-2020/county_day_ushigh_pm25_2020.csv')"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"id":"4645aa6c","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.136985Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.136476Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.163369Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.162743Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.035318,"end_time":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.164721+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-07-20T13:04:53.129403+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/html":["<div>\n","<style scoped>\n","    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n","        vertical-align: middle;\n","    }\n","\n","    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n","        vertical-align: top;\n","    }\n","\n","    .dataframe thead th {\n","        text-align: right;\n","    }\n","</style>\n","<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n","  <thead>\n","    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n","      <th></th>\n","      <th>county_fips</th>\n","      <th>date</th>\n","      <th>pm25_ushigh</th>\n","      <th>source</th>\n","    </tr>\n","  </thead>\n","  <tbody>\n","    <tr>\n","      <th>0</th>\n","      <td>1001</td>\n","      <td>2020-01-01<